Digital Performer defaults to keeping it's editing windows connected or ''consolidated''. If you would like to have the programs editing windows open in a stand-alone manner you need to deconsolidate them. 

To unconnect (deconsolidate) windows in [[Digital Performer]] go to '''Digital Performer/Preferences''' then go to '''Consolidated Windows''' and then deselect the box next to '''Enable Consolidated Editing'''.





